    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2158 <hi rend="superscript">5/6</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State (<persName
                            corresp="#p_WF1">White</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-30">August 30,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Argentine Ambassador, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EFA1">Espil</persName>,
                    called and showed me a cable from his Government which said that in view of the
                    fact that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Culbertson</persName> in Santiago had
                    found out about the proposed Argentine pact along the lines of the Kellogg Pact
                    and the Locarno Treaty<note n="4" xml:id="d273fn4">For texts of the agreements
                        signed at Locarno, October 16, 1925, see League of Nations Treaty Series,
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">liv</hi>, pp. 289 ff.</note> the Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs was sending <persName corresp="#p_EFA1">Espil</persName> by
                    air-mail <pb facs="0365" n="261" xml:id="pg_261"/> copies of this document to
                    submit to the Department. Their plan had been to take it up with the four
                    neighboring countries first and, after getting their agreement, then to submit
                    it to the Department, but in view of this fact they were sending it up now.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WF1">F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>] W[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">hite</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
